dspace-development.title: OAR: Missing Button for Metadata Review

comments.body:
I am currently able to view this button from within the staging environment:

![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5b5b6aed981c3204c9ed06c8/ddc176d1-d813-41c5-9b70-39874536af20)

While I find that I am a member of all of the following Groups:

![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5b5b6aed981c3204c9ed06c8/7d67b027-3836-47b9-a97b-2b6678b86d56)

...the user account for `hh4079` is not:

![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5b5b6aed981c3204c9ed06c8/552ae1e1-41fb-4b22-ac30-226bbacc0bfe)

While testing the adjustment of Group memberships, I have found that the affected user accounts should now have the proper permissions in the staging and production environments:

![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5b5b6aed981c3204c9ed06c8/346834df-f452-4e20-9039-a1e6374a5d2d)

I am going to proceed by requesting that the users test this in order to determine whether or not they have the necessary privileges.
Simply adding the affected users to these Groups did not resolve this for all Items. I will look to try and correctly diagnose this issue.

There are some differences Group memberships, but these, if anything, should be providing greater (rather than fewer) privileges:

![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5b5b6aed981c3204c9ed06c8/c8420f14-74ef-484d-a4cb-1009d57a8ccc)

Further reviewing Group membership, the following Groups do *not* have the affected users as members:

* COLLECTION_102_ADMIN
* COLLECTION_102_SUBMIT
* COLLECTION_102_WORKFLOW_STEP_2
* COLLECTION_103_WORKFLOW_STEP_2
* COLLECTION_103_WORKFLOW_STEP_3
* COLLECTION_104_ADMIN
* COLLECTION_104_SUBMIT
* COLLECTION_34_ADMIN
* COMMUNITY_All_ADMIN
* PU Affiliate
I have adjusted the membership for these Groups, and requested that the affected users test the feature within the production environment.

Unfortunately, this also did not resolve the errors. Further, the privileges must now be further adjusted, as the following was reported:

> I'm not sure if this is related, but the labels in our pool are showing new labelling that shouldn't be there. Our labels should only be "needs review" or "review".

`org.dspace.workflow.WorkflowManager` contains the functionality for managing the workflow state of the `WorkflowItem`, and currently one of the affected Items lies within the state of `WFSTATE_STEP2POOL` (value of `state` 3). This has the following description:

```
public static final int WFSTATE_STEP1 = 2; // task - reviewer has claimed it
public static final int WFSTATE_STEP2POOL = 3; // waiting for an admin to
                                                   // claim it
public static final int WFSTATE_STEP2 = 4; // task - admin has claimed item
```

As this WorkflowItem *does* have an owner, this might be a case in which the state was erroneously set to 2.

Serve mosaic document at mosaic endpoint
Ingest example raster dataset for mosaic.

comments.body:
The test set contains 4 directories: `1_scanned(ARK_dcwp988v99m)`, `2_georeferenced`, `3_clipped`, and `GeoTIFF_copy`. `1_scanned(ARK_dcwp988v99m)` contains a single tiff of each scan; each of the other directories contains multiple files per scan. I did a test ingesting the tiffs from the directory `GeoTIFF_copy`. I massaged them into the following directory structure:

```
└── raster_bulk_geotiffs_test
    └── 99125433518606421
        ├── Adrianople
        │   └── Adrianople.tif
        ├── Constantinople
        │   └── Constantinople.tif
        ├── Elbasan
        │   └── Elbasan.tif
        ├── Gallipoli
        │   └── Gallipoli.tif
        ├── Gumuljina
        │   └── Gumuljina.tif
        ├── Ipek
        │   └── Ipek.tif
        ├── Jumaa_i_Bala
        │   └── Jumaa_i_Bala.tif
        ├── Kirjali
        │   └── Kirjali.tif
        ├── Kozana
        │   └── Kozana.tif
        ├── Lemnos
        │   └── Lemnos.tif
        ├── Monastir
        │   └── Monastir.tif
        ├── Mt_Athos
        │   └── Mt_Athos.tif
        ├── Prishtina
        │   └── Prishtina.tif
        ├── Rodosto
        │   └── Rodosto.tif
        ├── Salonika
        │   └── Salonika.tif
        ├── Scutari
        │   └── Scutari.tif
        ├── Sofia
        │   └── Sofia.tif
        ├── Uskub
        │   └── Uskub.tif
        ├── Valona
        │   └── Valona.tif
        └── Vize
            └── Vize.tif
```

It created a RasterSet as expected, pulling in the metadata from the catalog as expected. Each member had a title taken from the name of the directory, as expected.

I did the same with the mix of tiffs and pngs from the `3_clipped` directory. These ingested with no errors but the png resources did not generate all the desired derivatives. They generated only an intermediate tiff.

![Screen Shot 2022-01-12 at 9.59.57 AM.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5cba1f45fec3b63424e0f761/7de8e9b1-4dc3-45bc-8e62-f5a78bdd43ec)

![Screen Shot 2022-01-12 at 10.02.31 AM.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5cba1f45fec3b63424e0f761/3fa0f026-17c4-4821-803d-d9b6461d8d0b)

I copied the ingest-ready / geotiffs-only directory to `hydra_sources/ingest_scratch/mosaic/raster_bulk_geotiffs_test` and then used that to create https://figgy-staging.princeton.edu/catalog/9a3dd626-d169-49b4-b6eb-c21132d0bd32
reopening - documentation piece not completed
I'm not 100% sure this is the right format yet either - we'll need an ingest that has both the collared and uncollared versions.
Should someone be available for review, this should be in a state to be merged please.

pulfalight.title: Viewer should not try to load downloadable audio files

comments.body:
Hi all! I ran into the discussion about this ticket on the digital_library thread and I'm experiencing a similar issue as Valencia. I figured I would leave this here as another example in case it's helpful for solving this issue, but let me know if there's a more appropriate place to report this. Thanks!

I recently added zips to Figgy for the four components that are children of this one: https://findingaids.princeton.edu/catalog/C1372_c217

Three of them successfully have the "View Content" button that leads to a zip file download, as expected (ex. https://findingaids.princeton.edu/catalog/C1372_c269), but for some reason this one displays a non-functional viewer instead of the "View Content" button and zip download (https://findingaids.princeton.edu/catalog/C1372_c272).

For that last one I had to delete the digital object in ASpace and switch the object to flagged then back to complete for the right DAO to sync over. We'll fix this in a more general way as part of resolving this during a maintenance cycle. That last one should be fixed the next time pulfalight indexes.
